Class AbstractLoginProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractLoginProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, ILogin
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LoginProxy

    public abstract class AbstractLoginProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements ILogin

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the Login. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    the username and password that correspond to a party and partner; the system verifies the identity of the party by comparison of the password given the username; note that the name changed from "User" because that was an Oracle keyword

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
